This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Obama and Prime Minister Roivas of Estonia to U.S. and Estonian servicemembers at Tallinn Airport Hangar in Estonia. The Prime Minister expressed pride in the Estonian soldiers and their alliance with the United States. He thanked the soldiers for their service and sacrifice in defending their way of life and common values. The President thanked the Prime Minister and expressed his appreciation for the Estonian and American servicemembers. He highlighted the historical alliance between the two countries and their shared commitment to NATO. The President reassured Estonia and other NATO Allies of the United States' support and defense. Both leaders expressed gratitude and pride in the servicemembers' dedication and commitment.